# Agent Model Strategy

Stria is a brand creating algorithmic music tools. First product: Drift (Max for Live phasing/interference engine with struck-bar physical modeling). Use these model preferences when the user hasn't specified one.

## By task type

| Task | Prefer |
|------|--------|
| **Phase math, drift, interference logic** | Claude 4.6 Opus |
| **Struck-bar synth design, modal synthesis** | Claude 4.6 Opus |
| **Step sequencer, M4L UI, device wiring** | Claude 4.5 Sonnet or GPT-5.3 Codex |
| **gen~ / RNBO C++ implementation** | Claude 4.5 Sonnet or Opus |
| **MVP planning, docs, research synthesis** | Claude 4.5 Sonnet (or Gemini 3 Pro + Max Mode for full-doc context) |
| **Bug fixes, small edits, boilerplate** | Gemini 3 Flash or GPT-5.3 Codex |

## Default

- **Primary**: Claude 4.5 Sonnet for most implementation work.
- **Heavy lifting**: Switch to Claude 4.6 Opus for synthesis design, timing, and architecture.
- **Budget**: Use Gemini 3 Flash or Grok Code for cheap, low-stakes tasks.

## Context

- Turn on **Max Mode** when the conversation needs the full MVP plan and research docs in context.
- Domain is niche (Max/MSP, RNBO, gen~, process music); Claude 4.x is generally more reliable than cheaper models for this stack.
